on (`.kiro/agents/entire.json`)\",\"-- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` — Hook event parsing\",\"-- `.github/workflows/e2e.yml:79-105` — CI workflow (AWS OIDC + SIGV4 setup)\",\"+If `kiro-cli whoami` doesn't populate the auth store, alternatives:\",\"+- Check if kiro-cli has a `login --sigv4` or `login --headless` command\",\"+- Write directly to kiro's SQLite auth store (fragile, version-dependent)\",\"+- Convert all multi-turn kiro tests to use sequential `RunPrompt` calls (loses multi-turn coverage)\",\" \",\" ## Verification\",\"-- Path A: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`, then CI E2E with `--agent kiro`\",\"-- Path B: depends on chosen sub-option; same verification steps after implementation\",\"+\",\"+1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\",\"+2. Test `RunPrompt` locally: `go test -tags e2e -run TestAttributionOnAgentCommit -v ./e2e/tests/ -agent kiro`\",\"+3. CI E2E with `--agent kiro` should pass\",\"+\",\"+## Key files\",\"+- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — only file modified\",\"+- `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` — reference for pipe-based `RunPrompt`\",\"+- `.github/workflows/e2e.yml:79-105` — CI env var setup\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Investigate: Kiro E2E auth failure persists after env forwarding fix\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe env-forwarding fix (commit `6c49b692`) wraps kiro-cli with `env KEY=VALUE ...` inside tmux, but CI still shows:\\n```\\nYou are not logged in. Login now?\\n```\\n\\nThe `env` wrapper approach is correct (matches Claude's pattern at `e2e/agents/claude.go:192`), so the issue is likely that **kiro-cli doesn't use SIGV4 env vars for its interactive login check**. It may only consult its own auth store (SQLite at `~/.local/share/kiro-cli/data.sqlite3`).\\n\\nThe user asks: can we use `--no-interactive` instead? The code comment at `e2e/agents/kiro.go:127` says hooks don't fire in that mode, but this was never verified.\\n\\n## Investigation: Verify `--no-interactive` hook behavior\\n\\n**We cannot verify from source code** — kiro-cli is a closed binary. The only reference is the comment at `kiro.go:127`:\\n```go\\n// kiro-cli --no-interactive mode does not fire agent hooks, so we must\\n// use interactive (tmux) mode and send the prompt through the TUI.\\n```\\n\\nThis needs empirical testing.\\n\\n### Quick empirical test (run locally or in CI)\\n\\nIn a repo with Entire kiro hooks installed (`.kiro/agents/entire.json`):\\n\\n```bash\\n# 1. Check if hooks fire with --no-interactive\\n# Watch for hook invocations (entire hooks kiro agent-spawn, etc.)\\nkiro-cli chat --no-interactive --agent entire -p \\\"Create a file called test.txt with hello\\\" 2>&1\\n\\n# 2. Check for .entire/tmp/kiro-active-session (written by agent-spawn hook)\\nls -la .entire/tmp/kiro-active-session\\n\\n# 3. Check .entire/logs/ for any hook activity\\nls -la .entire/logs/\\n```\\n\\nIf `kiro-active-session` exists after the run, hooks fired. If `.entire/logs/` has new entries, hooks fired.\\n\\n## Two paths forward depending on test results\\n\\n### Path A: `--no-interactive` DOES fire hooks\\n\\nRewrite `RunPrompt` to use pipe-based I/O (like Claude's `RunPrompt` at `claude.go:113-170`) instead of tmux:\\n\\n**File: `e2e/agents/kiro.go`**\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *Kiro) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n    // Use --no-interactive with pipe-based I/O (no tmux needed)\\n    args := []string{\\\"chat\\\", \\\"--no-interactive\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\", \\\"-p\\\", prompt}\\n    if cfg.Model != \\\"\\\" {\\n        args = append(args, \\\"--model\\\", cfg.Model)\\n    }\\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, k.Binary(), args...)\\n    cmd.Dir = dir\\n    // env vars propagate naturally via cmd.Env or os environment\\n    // ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n`StartSession` would still need tmux for multi-turn interactive sessions, but the SIGV4 env vars would propagate naturally through `exec.Command` for `RunPrompt`.\\n\\n### Path B: `--no-interactive` does NOT fire hooks (comment is correct)\\n\\nThe problem is that kiro-cli's interactive login check doesn't use SIGV4 env vars. Options:\\n\\n1. **Pre-authenticate before tmux** — run a kiro-cli command (e.g., `kiro-cli whoami`) with the SIGV4 env vars to populate the auth store, then launch the tmux session which reads from the same store\\n2. **Find a kiro-cli flag** — check `kiro-cli chat --help` for a flag like `--auth-mode sigv4` or `--skip-login-check`\\n3. **Write kiro auth config directly** — if kiro stores auth tokens in a known location, pre-populate it\\n\\n## Recommended next step\\n\\nRun the empirical test above to determine which path applies. This is the fastest way to unblock.\\n\\n## Key files\\n- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — E2E agent implementation (the file we modify)\\n- `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` — Claude's pipe-based `RunPrompt` (reference for Path A)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go` — Hook installation (`.kiro/agents/entire.json`)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/lifecycle.go` — Hook event parsing\\n- `.github/workflows/e2e.yml:79-105` — CI workflow (AWS OIDC + SIGV4 setup)\\n\\n## Verification\\n- Path A: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`, then CI E2E with `--agent kiro`\\n- Path B: depends on chosen sub-option; same verification steps after implementation\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"4576cde9-1b05-4948-bbdf-1c7b048e2f70\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"68120ced-9b8f-48c7-b42a-711d3aebb40f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01SSvyxE8nAV5dY7vsm6riAK\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01FeCQCa7jtTBSws27foHz5e\",\"name\":\"AskUserQuestion\",\"input\":{\"questions\":[{\"question\":\"For