go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code post-task\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01LEsxwfZ9MWJrbKeVbRzCa7\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01LEsxwfZ9MWJrbKeVbRzCa7\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T19:00:06.955Z\",\"uuid\":\"5e58e1ce-8959-4323-aba2-fc3092a13744\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"61a31d8c-e527-43d6-87bd-e6ac0eb57f80\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01LEsxwfZ9MWJrbKeVbRzCa7\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Perfect! I've now thoroughly reviewed all the files in the setup-kiro-action repository. Let me provide you with a comprehensive analysis:\\n\\n## Comprehensive Analysis of setup-kiro-action\\n\\n### Overview\\n`setup-kiro-action` is a **GitHub Actions composite action** that installs and caches the Kiro CLI (Amazon Q Developer CLI) for CI/CD workflows with **headless IAM authentication support via SIGV4**.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. How SIGV4 Authentication is Set Up\\n\\n**Location:** `action.yml` lines 125-130\\n\\n```yaml\\n- name: Configure SIGV4 authentication\\n  if: inputs.enable-sigv4 == 'true'\\n  shell: bash\\n  run: |\\n    echo \\\"AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=true\\\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\\n    echo \\\"AWS_REGION=${{ inputs.aws-region }}\\\" >> $GITHUB_ENV\\n```\\n\\n**Key Points:**\\n- **SIGV4 is enabled via two environment variables only:**\\n  - `AMAZON_Q_SIGV4=true` - Tells Kiro CLI to use AWS SigV4 signing\\n  - `AWS_REGION=<region>` - Specifies the AWS region (default: `us-east-1`)\\n- **No config file creation** - SIGV4 is purely environment-variable-based\\n- **No login step** - SIGV4 relies on ambient AWS credentials from the GitHub Actions environment\\n- **Discovered feature** - The README explicitly notes this is an \\\"undocumented feature\\\" discovered through source code analysis of amazon-q-developer-cli\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Authentication Methods in CI/CD\\n\\nThe action supports **two authentication patterns** (from README):\\n\\n#### **Method 1: OIDC (Recommended for GitHub Actions)**\\n- Uses GitHub's OIDC provider for secure, ephemeral credentials\\n- **Requires setup:**\\n  1. Create OIDC provider in AWS\\n  2. Create IAM role with trust policy\\n  3. Use `aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v5` to assume the role\\n  4. Enable SIGV4 in the action\\n\\n**Example workflow (tier1-maximum-security.yml):**\\n```yaml\\npermissions:\\n  id-token: write\\n\\n- uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v5\\n  with:\\n    role-to-assume: ${{ secrets.AWS_ROLE_ARN }}\\n    aws-region: us-east-1\\n\\n- uses: clouatre-labs/setup-kiro-action@v1\\n  with:\\n    enable-sigv4: true\\n    aws-region: us-east-1\\n```\\n\\n#### **Method 2: IAM User Credentials (Local Development)**\\n- Uses long-lived AWS credentials stored as secrets\\n- **WARNING:** Do NOT use `enable-sigv4: true` with long-lived credentials (AKIA* keys)\\n\\n```yaml\\n- uses: clouatre-labs/setup-kiro-action@v1\\n  # No enable-sigv4 here\\n\\n- name: Use Kiro CLI\\n  env:\\n    AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}\\n    AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}\\n    AWS_REGION: us-east-1\\n  run: kiro-cli-chat chat --no-interactive \\\"What is 2+2?\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Kiro CLI Binary Installation\\n\\n**Location:** `action.yml` lines 58-116\\n\\nThe action:\\n1. **Downloads** the precompiled Kiro CLI binary from AWS CDN:\\n   ```\\n   https://desktop-release.q.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/{version}/kirocli-{arch}-linux.zip\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Supports architecture detection:**\\n   - X64 → `x86_64`\\n   - ARM64 → `aarch64`\\n\\n3. **Optionally verifies SHA256 checksum** (if `verify-checksum: true`)\\n\\n4. **Caches the binary** at `~/.local/bin/kiro-cli-chat` for subsequent