IGV4 env vars for auth. This means:\\n- `RunPrompt` can switch to pipe-based `--no-interactive` mode (simpler, no tmux)\\n- `StartSession` still needs tmux (multi-turn), but needs a different auth fix\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### File: `e2e/agents/kiro.go`\\n\\n#### 1. Rewrite `RunPrompt` to use `--no-interactive` (pipe-based, no tmux)\\n\\nModel after Claude's `RunPrompt` at `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` which uses `exec.CommandContext` with pipes.\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *Kiro) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n    cfg := &runConfig{}\\n    for _, o := range opts {\\n        o(cfg)\\n    }\\n\\n    timeout := 2 * time.Minute\\n    if cfg.PromptTimeout > 0 {\\n        timeout = cfg.PromptTimeout\\n    }\\n\\n    args := []string{\\\"chat\\\", \\\"--no-interactive\\\", \\\"--trust-all-tools\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\", prompt}\\n    if cfg.Model != \\\"\\\" {\\n        args = append(args, \\\"--model\\\", cfg.Model)\\n    }\\n\\n    cmdCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, timeout)\\n    defer cancel()\\n\\n    cmd := exec.CommandContext(cmdCtx, k.Binary(), args...)\\n    cmd.Dir = dir\\n    // No need for env wrapper — exec.Command inherits process env (including SIGV4 vars)\\n\\n    var stdout, stderr strings.Builder\\n    cmd.Stdout = &stdout\\n    cmd.Stderr = &stderr\\n\\n    err := cmd.Run()\\n    exitCode := 0\\n    if err != nil {\\n        exitErr := &exec.ExitError{}\\n        if errors.As(err, &exitErr) {\\n            exitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\\n        } else {\\n            exitCode = -1\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    return Output{\\n        Command:  k.Binary() + \\\" \\\" + strings.Join(args, \\\" \\\"),\\n        Stdout:   stdout.String(),\\n        Stderr:   stderr.String(),\\n        ExitCode: exitCode,\\n    }, err\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Why this works:**\\n- `exec.CommandContext` inherits the Go process's env vars (SIGV4 included)\\n- No tmux → no env-forwarding issue\\n- `--no-interactive` fires hooks (verified empirically)\\n- `--trust-all-tools` replaces the interactive `-a` flag\\n\\n**Note:** Need to verify the exact flag name. User's test showed `--trust-all-tools` in the error message. Also need to verify prompt passing — the user's test used a positional arg, not `-p`.\\n\\n#### 2. Fix `StartSession` auth with pre-authentication\\n\\nBefore launching the tmux session, run a quick `--no-interactive` command to warm up kiro-cli's auth store:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (k *Kiro) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n    // Pre-authenticate: run a no-op kiro-cli command so SIGV4 env vars\\n    // populate the auth store for the subsequent interactive session.\\n    if os.Getenv(\\\"AMAZON_Q_SIGV4\\\") != \\\"\\\" {\\n        authCtx, authCancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, 10*time.Second)\\n        defer authCancel()\\n        authCmd := exec.CommandContext(authCtx, k.Binary(), \\\"whoami\\\")\\n        authCmd.Dir = dir\\n        _ = authCmd.Run() // best-effort; interactive session will retry auth\\n    }\\n\\n    name := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"kiro-test-%d\\\", time.Now().UnixNano())\\n    cmdArgs := append([]string{\\\"env\\\"}, kiroAuthEnvArgs()...)\\n    cmdArgs = append(cmdArgs, k.Binary(), \\\"chat\\\", \\\"-a\\\", \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"entire\\\")\\n    s, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, []string{\\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY\\\"}, cmdArgs[0], cmdArgs[1:]...)\\n    // ...\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Caveat:** This assumes `kiro-cli whoami` with SIGV4 env vars populates the local auth store. If it doesn't, this won't help and we'll need an alternative approach (see fallback below).\\n\\n#### 3. Update the wrong comment\\n\\n```go\\n// Remove this incorrect comment:\\n// kiro-cli --no-interactive mode does not fire agent hooks, so we must\\n// use interactive (tmux) mode and send the prompt through the TUI.\\n```\\n\\n#### 4. Keep `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper (for `StartSession`'s tmux env forwarding)\\n\\nThe helper from the previous commit stays — it's still needed for `StartSession`'s tmux wrapper.\\n\\n### Fallback if pre-auth doesn't work for `StartSession`\\n\\nIf `kiro-cli whoami` doesn't populate the auth store, alternatives:\\n- Check if kiro-cli has a `login --sigv4` or `login --headless` command\\n- Write directly to kiro's SQLite auth store (fragile, version-dependent)\\n- Convert all multi-turn kiro tests to use sequential `RunPrompt` calls (loses multi-turn coverage)\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Test `RunPrompt` locally: `go test -tags e2e -run TestAttributionOnAgentCommit -v ./e2e/tests/ -agent kiro`\\n3. CI E2E with `--agent kiro` should pass\\n\\n## Key files\\n- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — only file modified\\n- `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` — reference for pipe-based `RunPrompt`\\n- `.github/workflows/e2e.yml:79-105` — CI env var setup\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"0413768b-e135-4553-8f84-c6fafaed1599\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"80551555-07f3-419a-aa40-3e172fc46a9d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/kiro-oneshot\",\"sessionId\":\"a6375286-82fb-48a9-90fd-f8e611e47d1b\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/kiro-oneshot\",\"slug\":\"snappy-yawning-swan\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_016VV9H1sjE4Fiw1yiq3YsFy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me verify the `Session` interface so the plan is accurate.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2901,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":122245,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2901},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYkT2kC6HwMX1H6dV7UMk\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"49b3f2f8-10ff-4134-ad87-b11507c4b8fd\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T19:01:09.379Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\"