ssion) WaitFor(_ string, _ time.Duration) (string, error) {\\n    return s.lastOutput, nil  // command already completed in Send\\n}\\n\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Capture() string { return s.lastOutput }\\nfunc (s *KiroSession) Close() error    { return nil }\\n```\\n\\n**Session interface** (`e2e/agents/agent.go:57-62`): `Send`, `WaitFor`, `Capture`, `Close`\\n\\n**Trade-off:** Each `Send` creates a separate kiro-cli process (separate agent-spawn/stop hooks). Multi-turn tests will exercise multiple single-turn sessions instead of one continuous session. This is acceptable because:\\n- Hooks still fire correctly per prompt\\n- File changes persist (same working directory)\\n- The alternative (interactive TUI) doesn't work with SIGV4 at all\\n- Single-turn is how `setup-kiro-action` uses kiro-cli in CI\\n\\n#### 3. Remove dead code\\n- Delete `kiroAuthEnvArgs()` helper (no longer needed without tmux)\\n- Delete incorrect comment about `--no-interactive` not firing hooks\\n- Remove the old `KiroSession` struct that wrapped `TmuxSession`\\n\\n#### 4. Adjust imports\\n- Keep: `context`, `encoding/json`, `errors`, `fmt`, `os`, `os/exec`, `strings`, `time`\\n- Remove if no longer used: any tmux-only imports\\n\\n## What stays the same\\n- `Bootstrap()` — validates SIGV4 env vars in CI (unchanged)\\n- Hook installation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/`) — unchanged\\n- CI workflows (`.github/workflows/e2e.yml`) — unchanged\\n- All other agent implementations — unchanged\\n\\n## Verification\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. CI E2E with `--agent kiro` should pass\\n\\n## Key files\\n- `e2e/agents/kiro.go` — only file modified\\n- `e2e/agents/claude.go:113-170` — reference for pipe-based `RunPrompt`\\n- `e2e/agents/agent.go:57-62` — `Session` interface\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2726,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":131260,\"output_t